Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "debela" in different forms and positions:

1. *Debela* knjiga leži na stolu. (A *thick* book is lying on the table.)
2. Ona je *debelja* od mene. (She is *fatter* than me.)
3. *Debela* žena je ušla u prodavnicu. (A *fat* woman entered the store.)
4. On ima *debelu* novčaniku. (He has a *thick* wallet.)
5. Spremi se, napolju je *debela* magla. (Get ready, there is a *thick* fog outside.)
6. Nemoj da jedeš previše slatkiša, postaćeš *debela*. (Don't eat too much candy, you'll become *fat*.)
7. Ova haljina mi je pre *debel* struk. (This dress is too *thick* around the waist for me.)
8. *Debela* linija razdvaja dve trake. (A *thick* line separates two lanes.)
9. Vidiš li onu *debelu* granu na drvetu? (Do you see that *thick* branch on the tree?)
10. Moramo da upotrebimo *debele* rukavice da bismo zaštitili ruke. (We need to use *thick* gloves to protect our hands.)

I hope this helps!